tr.th: Conclusion and Recommendations based on this report and previous findings known to us

tr.td: Most parameters are within normal limits. Notable findings include elevated total cholesterol and triglycerides, and low HDL cholesterol, indicating increased cardiovascular risk. The total CO₂ is slightly low, which may suggest mild metabolic acidosis but should be correlated clinically. Glucose and HbA1c are within acceptable ranges. Renal function and microalbumin/creatinine ratio are normal. Recommend addressing dyslipidemia and monitoring acid-base status as clinically indicated.
